I think you should actually prove
```suggestion
    (Ico a b).filter (r  ) = (Ico a / (r : ) b / (r : )).map (.mulRight r) := by
```
Or similar

That was in fact how my original proof went (_separately_ establishing equality of sets), but @b-mehta (when I presented the declaration for golfing on Xena) thought that _integrating_ the equivalence proof into the cardinality theorem through `card_congr` was better. I agreed with him.

https://discord.com/channels/679792285910827018/714579217274110003/1190477890064748685
never mind, your suggestion turns out to be even shorter.

Why not
```suggestion
    (Ico (a / r) (b / r)).map _, mul_left_injective hr.ne' := by
```
Am I missing an obvious reason why you need to round up and not down?
Ah nevermind, I see why
Can you add the Ioc version too?
Added!
That's a weird file name for this
I don't know a better name  or home  for this actually.
@YaelDillies do you have any advice on this matter?
CardIntervalMod, for instance?

```suggestion
    (Ico a / (r : ) b / (r : )).map ( * r), mul_left_injective hr.ne' := by
```
It doesn't help Lean, but it definitely helps the reader understand what the theorem is saying.
